78 or medical product or device for all similar pharmacies in the network as determined by
79 the pharmacy benefits manager within 3 business days.
80 (l) A pharmacy benefits manager or covered entity shall make available on its secure web
81 site information about the appeals process, including, but not limited to, a telephone number or
82 process that a pharmacy may use to submit cost appeals. The medical products and devices
83 subject to the requirements of this part are limited to the medical products and devices included
84 as a pharmacy benefit under the pharmacy benefits contract.
85 (m) A pharmacy shall not disclose to any third party the cost lists and any related
86 information it receives from a pharmacy benefits manager or covered entity; provided, a
87 pharmacy may share such lists and related information with a pharmacy services administrative
88 organization or similar entity with which the pharmacy has a contract to provide administrative
89 services for that pharmacy. If a pharmacy shares this information with a pharmacy services
90 administrative organization or similar entity, that organization or entity shall not disclose the
91 information to any third party.
92 (n) A pharmacy benefits manager or covered entity is prohibited from applying
93 retroactive discounts including but not limited to Generic Effective Rate and Brand Effective
94 Rate. All discounts must be applied when the claim is paid.
95 (o) A pharmacy benefits manager or covered entity shall include payment for covered
96 medications in its explanation of benefits
97 SECTION 1. Section 9B of chapter 118E of the General Laws, is hereby amended by
