99 All MassHealth Managed Care Organizations and Accountable Care Organizations are
100 required to reimburse pharmacies at the same rate as described in the MassHealth Pharmacy
101 Provider Manual.
102 The Insurance Commissioner shall enforce this Act and shall promulgate regulations to
103 enforce the provisions of this act. The commissioner may examine or audit the books and records
104 of a pharmacy benefits manager providing claims processing services or other prescription drug
105 or device services for a health benefit plan to determine if the pharmacy benefits manager is in
106 compliance with this Act. The information or data acquired during an examination is:
107 (i) Considered proprietary and confidential; and
108 (ii) Not subject to the Freedom of Information Act of Massachusetts
109 (o) In any participation contracts between pharmacy benefits managers and pharmacists
110 or pharmacies providing prescription drug coverage for health benefit plans, no pharmacy or
111 pharmacist may be prohibited, restricted, or penalized in any way from disclosing to any covered
112 person any healthcare information that the pharmacy or pharmacist deems appropriate regarding
113 the nature of treatment, risks, or alternatives thereto, the availability of alternate therapies,
114 consultations, or tests, the decision of utilization reviewers or similar persons to authorize or
115 deny services, the process that is used to authorize or deny healthcare services or benefits, or
116 information on financial incentives and structures used by the insurer.
117 (p) Further any such contract as stated above shall not prohibit a pharmacist or pharmacy
118 from providing an insured individual information on the amount of the insured's cost share for
119 such insured's prescription drug and the clinical efficacy of a more affordable alternative drug if
120 one is available. Neither a pharmacy nor a pharmacist shall be penalized by a pharmacy benefits
